# No Duplicate Quotes

When adding a quote to the book, always check if it's already used elsewhere first (search for the author name or key phrase). Each quote should appear exactly once.

- If a quote is already in the book and the user references it for a new location, decide which placement is stronger and use it there only.
- If the new location is better, move it (remove from old location, add to new).
- If the original location is better, keep it there and link to it instead.
- Never copy a quote into a second location. The user considers this a significant quality issue.
